---
title: "isValidSignature (Payment Abstraction V2)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_decode: decode order from signature data
    q_decode --> q_check_auction: extract (sellToken, buyToken, sellAmount, buyAmount, receiver)

    q_check_auction --> q_invalid: no live auction for sellToken
    q_check_auction --> q_check_sell_token: live auction exists

    q_check_sell_token --> q_invalid: sellToken not in allowlistedAssets
    q_check_sell_token --> q_check_buy_token: sellToken is allowlisted

    q_check_buy_token --> q_invalid: buyToken != s_assetOut
    q_check_buy_token --> q_check_receiver: buyToken == s_assetOut

    q_check_receiver --> q_invalid: receiver != address(this)
    q_check_receiver --> q_check_amount: receiver == address(this)

    q_check_amount --> q_invalid: sellAmount == 0
    q_check_amount --> q_check_price: sellAmount > 0

    q_check_price --> q_calc_min: get current auction price via getAssetOutAmount
    q_calc_min --> q_check_min_buy: minBuyAmount = getAssetOutAmount(sellAmount)

    q_check_min_buy --> q_invalid: buyAmount < minBuyAmount
    q_check_min_buy --> q_valid: buyAmount >= minBuyAmount

    q_valid --> [*]: return EIP1271_MAGIC_VALUE
    q_invalid --> [*]: return INVALID_SIGNATURE

    note right of q_check_price
        INV-012: isValidSignature enforces auction price as minimum buy amount
        INV-013: only the auction contract itself can be the receiver
        INV-014: buyToken must be s_assetOut (LINK)
        INV-015: sellAmount must be > 0 to prevent zero-amount orders
    end note
